\;V:=\Bbb R_n[x]=
\;n\;
\;\dim_{\Bbb R}V=n+1\;
f(x)=a_0+a_1x+\ldots+a_nx^n\;:\;f(0)=f(2)\iff a_0=a_0+2a_1+4a_2+\ldots+2^na_n\implies
a_1+2a_2+\ldots+2^{n-1}a_n=0
H=\ker\phi\;,\;\;\text{with}\;\;\phi:V\to \Bbb R\;\;\text{defined by}\;\;\phi(p(x)):=p(2)-p(0)
\;H\;
\{1,\;2x-x^2\;,\;4x-x^3\,,\,8x-x^4\,,\,\ldots,2^{n-1}x-x^n\;\}
